/*
  dotWatch ESP32-DHT3 Hardened Firmware
  Phase 4F

  This firmware is for the additional model:
    model_key  = esp32_dht3
    model_name = ESP32-DHT3

  It does NOT replace Raspberry Pi / DW20CH.

  Metrics:
    metric_1 = Temperature (°C)
    metric_2 = Humidity (%)
    metric_3 = WiFi RSSI (dBm)

  Setup portal:
    SSID: dotWatch-ESP32-Setup
    URL : http://192.168.4.1/

  Phase 4F hardening:
    - No hardcoded Wi-Fi/device secret
    - Config stored in ESP32 Preferences/NVS
    - Status LED
    - BOOT long-press reset config
    - Wi-Fi reconnect and self-recovery restart
    - Last send/error snapshot in portal and JSON
    - Numeric metric payload

  Phase 4H local admin:
    - Local web admin over normal Wi-Fi IP
    - PIN-protected config changes on LAN
    - Edit Wi-Fi/backend/device/DHT settings without factory reset

  Phase 5A TLS hardening:
    - Optional Root CA certificate from Local Admin Portal
    - Uses setCACert() when Root CA is configured
    - Production default blocks insecure TLS fallback when Root CA is empty

  Phase 10B TLS CA provisioning:
    - Supports embedded Root CA generated by scripts/phase10b-esp32-install-root-ca.ps1
    - Portal Root CA overrides embedded Root CA when configured
    - Keeps production HTTPS verification on by default
*/

